column209: the description of death seems written by a human

column17: If someone told me that they lived every life or something I'd brush them off and laugh at them instead of believing them. I believe most people would do the same.

column80: I thought the reaction from the humans in the story was very realistic because humans usually have to work 40 hours a week just to sustain a living and sometimes even more. Additionally, it cost hundreds of dollars to pay for medical care. Thus, the humans were filled with joy from having all of their needs met by the aliens for only working 16 hours a week. The real world is usually much more cutthroat but the aliens don't know that. So I think that the story was likely written by a human because of the connection to the real world and the humans thinking there is a catch.

column51: I was actually kind of unsure about whether this was written by an LLM or a human until the ending.
